    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The folks from Google strike again with Inception-v4, <strong>43M</strong> parameters. Again, this is an improvement from Inception-v3. The main difference is the Stem group and some minor changes in the Inception-C module. The authors also ‚Äúmade uniform choices for the Inception blocks for each grid size.‚Äù They also mentioned that having ‚Äúresidual connections leads to dramatically improved training speed.‚Äù</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">All in all, note that it was mentioned that Inception-v4 works better because of the increased model size.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
