    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If you‚Äôre thinking about ResNets, yes, they are related. ResNeXt-50 has <strong>25M</strong> parameters (ResNet-50 has 25.5M). What‚Äôs different about ResNeXts is the adding of parallel towers/branches/paths within each module, as seen above indicated by ‚Äòtotal 32 towers.‚Äô</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>‚≠êÔ∏è What‚Äôs novel?</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ol><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Scaling up the number of parallel towers (‚Äúcardinality‚Äù) within a module (well I mean this has already been explored by the Inception network, except that these towers are added here)</li></ol></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>üìùPublication</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ul><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Paper: <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.05431" target="_self">Aggregated Residual Transformations for Deep Neural Networks</a></li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Authors: Saining Xie, Ross Girshick, Piotr Doll√°r, Zhuowen Tu, Kaiming He. University of California San Diego, Facebook Research</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Published in: 2017 IEEE Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (CVPR)</li></ul></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7"><strong>Appendix: Network In Network (2014)</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Recall that in a convolution, the value of a pixel is a linear combination of the weights in a filter and the current sliding window. The authors proposed that instead of this linear combination, let‚Äôs have a mini neural network with 1 hidden layer. This is what they coined as Mlpconv. So what we‚Äôre dealing with here is a (simple 1 hidden layer) network in a (convolutional neural) network.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">This idea of Mlpconv is likened to 1√ó1 convolutions and later became the main feature for Inception architectures.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>‚≠êÔ∏èWhat‚Äôs novel?</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
